dfrapStatusDteTxLED.description: Status of the DTE Tx Data LED. In Frame Relay mode, this LED is ON (green) when the DTE is not sending HDLC Flags and is OFF when HDLC flags are being transmit. In CBO mode, the LED is ON (green) for a SPACE and OFF for a MARK. (1) DTE Transmit LED OFF: inactive (HDLC flags or CBO marks) (2) DTE Transmit LED ON: active (HDLC frames or CBO spaces)

dfrapStatusDteRxLED.name: dfrapStatusDteRxLED
dfrapStatusDteRxLED.description: Status of the DTE Rx Data LED. In Frame Relay mode, this LED is ON (green) when the WAN is receiving HDLC Flags and is OFF when HDLC flags are being received. In CBO mode, the LED is ON (green) for a SPACE and OFF for a MARK. (1) DTE Receive LED OFF: inactive (HDLC flags or CBO marks) (2) DTE Receive LED ON: active (HDLC frames or CBO spaces)

dfrapStatusDdsModeLED.name: dfrapStatusDdsModeLED
dfrapStatusDdsModeLED.description: Status of the DDS Mode LED. (1) DDS Mode LED is green: normal data mode (2) DDS Mode LED is yellow: test mode

dfrapStatusDdsStatusLED.name: dfrapStatusDdsStatusLED
dfrapStatusDdsStatusLED.description: Status of the DDS Status LED. (1) DDS Status LED is OFF: no signal received from WAN (2) DDS Status LED is green: normal (3) DDS Status LED is yellow: remote alarm

dfrapStatusAllLEDs.name: dfrapStatusAllLEDs
dfrapStatusAllLEDs.description: Status of all six DFRAP LEDs, encoded in a string. 'F' off '5' green '0' yellow 'A' red '7' blinking green and off '3' blinking yellow and off 'B' blinking red and off '4' blinking green and yellow '6' blinking green and red '8' blinking yellow and red Positionally, the 6 letters are DTE Mode, DTE status, Dte Tx, Dte Rx, DDS Mode, and DDS Status. For example, '555550' would mean: DTE in normal mode, active status, transmitting and receiving and DDS normal with remote alarm.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInOctets.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInOctets
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInOctets.description: The count of all management octets received. Same as ifInOctets in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInErrors.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInErrors
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInErrors.description: The count of management packets received that could not be delivered because of errors. Same as ifInErrors in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOutOctets.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOutOctets
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOutOctets.description: The count of all management octets transmitted. Same as ifOutOctets in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOperStatus.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOperStatus
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOperStatus.description: The current operational state. Same as ifOperStatus in mib-2. (1) link up (2) link down (30 test

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInRcv.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInRcv
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInRcv.description: The count of all management datagrams received. Same as ipInReceives in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInHdrErr.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInHdrErr
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInHdrErr.description: The count of management datagrams received that were discarded because of errors in their IP headers. Same as ipInHdrErrors in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInAddrErr.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInAddrErr
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInAddrErr.description: The count of management datagrams received that were discarded because unexpected or invalid IP addresses in their IP headers. Same as ipInAddrErrors in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInProtUnk.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInProtUnk
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInProtUnk.description: The count of management datagrams received that were discarded because of unsupported protocols. Same as ipInUnknownProtos in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDscrd.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDscrd
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDscrd.description: The count of management datagrams received that were discarded for reasons other than a problem with the datagram. Same as ipInDiscards in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDlvrs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDlvrs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDlvrs.description: The count of management datagrams received that were delivered to IP client-protocols. Same as ipInDelivers in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutRqst.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutRqst
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutRqst.description: The count of all outgoing management datagrams originating in this node. Same as ipOutRequests in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutDscrd.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutDscrd
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutDscrd.description: The count of outgoing management datagrams that were discarded for reasons other than a problem with the datagram. Same as ipOutDiscards in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutNoRt.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutNoRt
dfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutNoRt.description: The count of outgoing management datagrams that were discarded because no route could be found for transmission. Same as ipOutNoRoutes in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInMsgs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInMsgs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInMsgs.description: The count of all management ICMP messages received. Same as icmpInMsgs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInErrors.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInErrors
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInErrors.description: The count of management ICMP messages received with errors. Same as icmpInErrors in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInDestUnreachs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInDestUnreachs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInDestUnreachs.description: The count of management ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received. Same as icmpInDestUnreachs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInTimeExcds.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInTimeExcds
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInTimeExcds.description: The count of management ICMP Time Exceeded messages received. Same as icmpInTimeExcds in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInParmProbs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInParmProbs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInParmProbs.description: The count of management ICMP Parameter Problem messages received. Same as icmpInParmProbs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInRedirects.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInRedirects
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInRedirects.description: The count of management ICMP Redirect messages received. Same as icmpInRedirects in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchos.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchos
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchos.description: The count of management ICMP Echo messages received. Same as icmpInEchos in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchoReps.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchoReps
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchoReps.description: The count of management ICMP Echo Reply messages received. Same as icmpInEchoReps in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutMsgs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutMsgs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutMsgs.description: The count of all outgoing management ICMP messages originating in this node. Same as icmpOutMsgs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutErrors.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutErrors
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutErrors.description: The count of outgoing management ICMP messages not transmitted due problems found by the ICMP layer. which this entity did Same as icmpOutErrors in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutDestUnreachs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutDestUnreachs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutDestUnreachs.description: The count of outgoing management ICMP Destination Unreachable messages. Same as icmpOutDestUnreachs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutParmProbs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutParmProbs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutParmProbs.description: The count of outgoing management ICMP Parameter Problem messages. Same as icmpOutParmProbs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutRedirects.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutRedirects
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutRedirects.description: The count of outgoing management ICMP Redirect messages. Same as icmpOutRedirects in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchos.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchos
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchos.description: The count of management outgoing ICMP Echo messages. Same as icmpOutEchos in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchoReps.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchoReps
dfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchoReps.description: The count of management outgoing ICMP Echo Reply messages. Same as icmpOutEchoReps in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPInDatagrams.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPInDatagrams
dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPInDatagrams.description: The count of all management UDP datagrams received. Same as udpInDatagrams in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPOutDatagrams.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPOutDatagrams
dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPOutDatagrams.description: The count of all management UDP datagrams sent. Same as udpOutDatagrams in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPNoPorts.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPNoPorts
dfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPNoPorts.description: The count of all management UDP datagrams received with no application at the destination port. Same as udpNoPorts in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPActiveOpens.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPActiveOpens
dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPActiveOpens.description: The count of the times management TCP connections have made a direct state transition from CLOSED to SYN-SENT. Same as tcpActiveOpens in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPPassiveOpens.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPPassiveOpens
dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPPassiveOpens.description: The count of the times management TCP connections have made a direct state transition from CLOSED to SYN-RCVD. Same as tcpPassiveOpens in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPAttemptFails.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPAttemptFails
dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPAttemptFails.description: The count of the times management TCP connections have made a direct state transition from SYN-SENT or SYN-RCVD to CLOSED state, plus the count of the times TCP connections have made a direct state transition from SYN-RCVD to LISTEN. Same as tcpAttemptFails in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPCurrEstab.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPCurrEstab
dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPCurrEstab.description: The count of the management TCP connections in state ESTABLISHED or CLOSE-WAIT. Same as tcpCurrEstab in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPInSegs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPInSegs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPInSegs.description: The count of all the management segments received. Same as tcpInSegs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPOutSegs.name: dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPOutSegs
dfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPOutSegs.description: The count of all the management segments sent. Same as tcpOutSegs in mib-2.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTable.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTable
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTable.description: The throughput per interface table. These values are accumulated across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfEntry.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfEntry
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfEntry.description: An entry in the throughput per interface table.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfIndex.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfIndex
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfIndex.description: Interface for which the statistics apply. (1) DTE interface (2) DDS interface

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxByteCnt.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxByteCnt
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxByteCnt.description: The number of framed bytes that have been received on this interface.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxByteCnt.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxByteCnt
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxByteCnt.description: The number of framed bytes that have been transmit on this interface.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxFrameCnt.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxFrameCnt
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxFrameCnt.description: The number of frames that have been received on this interface.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxFrameCnt.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxFrameCnt
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxFrameCnt.description: The number of frames that have been transmit on this interface.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxCrcErrCnt.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxCrcErrCnt
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxCrcErrCnt.description: The number of frames with CRC errors received on this interface.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxAbortCnt.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxAbortCnt
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxAbortCnt.description: The number of aborted frames received on this interface.

dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxBpvCnt.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxBpvCnt
dfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxBpvCnt.description: The number of BPV errors received on this interface.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTable.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTable
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTable.description: Layer 2 statistics on a per-DLCI basis. Transmit direction is from DTE to WAN and receive direction is from the WAN towards the DTE.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEntry.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEntry
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEntry.description: The Statistics for a particular Data Link Connection Management Interface (DLCI).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciIndex.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciIndex
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciIndex.description: This value must be in the range 1-3. Other than that, this value is ignored as all three will return the same result.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciValue.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciValue
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciValue.description: The DLCI value in which the Statistics are associated.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCreateTime.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCreateTime
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCreateTime.description: The amount of time elapsed since this DLCI was first detected through traffic sensing or in an LMI message (in seconds).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciChangeTime.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciChangeTime
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciChangeTime.description: The amount of elapsed time since this DLCI last changed state from active to inactive or vice versa (in seconds).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxByte.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxByte
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxByte.description: The number of bytes that have been received from the WAN towards the DTE on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxByte.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxByte
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxByte.description: The number of bytes that have been transmit from the DTE towards the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFrame.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFrame
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFrame.description: The number of frames that have been received from the WAN towards to the DTE on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxFrame.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxFrame
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxFrame.description: The number of frames that have been transmit from the DTE towards the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFecn.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFecn
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFecn.description: The number frames received from the WAN towards the DTE that have had the Forward Explict Congestion Notification (FECN) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxBecn.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxBecn
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxBecn.description: The number frames received from the WAN towards the DTE that have had the Backward Explict Congestion Notification (BECN) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxDe.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxDe
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxDe.description: The number frames received from the WAN towards the DTE that have had the Discard Eligibility (DE) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxDe.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxDe
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxDe.description: The number frames transmit towards the WAN from the DTE that have had the Discard Eligibility (DE) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxThruput.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxThruput
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxThruput.description: The number of bits/sec received from the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxThruput.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxThruput
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxThruput.description: The number of bits/sec transmit to the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCIR.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCIR
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCIR.description: The Committed Information Rate (CIR) for this DLCI. This can come form one of three sources: From the LMI Full Status Response, configured by the user, or the DTE line rate (default).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCirType.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCirType
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCirType.description: The source of the CIR value for this DLCI. (1) CIR acquired from LMI message. Will override user configured CIR. This feature is not supported by all Frame Relay DCE (switches). (2) CIR configured by user. (3) CIR is DTE Line Rate. Default if CIR is not set by one of the other methods.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciUptime.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciUptime
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciUptime.description: The total amount of time that the DLCI has been up as reproted by the LMI Full Status Response (in seconds).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciDowntime.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciDowntime
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciDowntime.description: The total amount of time that the DLCI has been declared down (in seconds). A DLCI is Down if it's explicitly declared Inactive through LMI or if it's missing from the LMI Full Status message or if there is no Full Status message at all.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState.description: The current state of the DLCI: (1) DLCI marked active in last full status LMI (2) DLCI in last full status LMI but not marked active (3) DLCI has never been seen in a full status LMI (4) DLCI was seen at least once in a full status LMI but was not in the last full status LMI (5) the full status LMI has timed out; all previously active or inactive DLCIs are changed to this state (6) DLCI was detected in the traffic stream and a full status LMI has not been received so the state cannot be determined yet.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciOutageCount.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciOutageCount
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciOutageCount.description: The number of times the smperPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState transitions from pvc-active or pvc-undetermined to one of the other (inactive) states.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciAvailability.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciAvailability
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciAvailability.description: The measure of the percentage time the DLCI is available: UpTime/CreateTime or zero if CreateTime = 0. (in 1/1000 per cent; i.e. availability = 1000 converts to 1%).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTBSO.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTBSO
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTBSO.description: Mean Time Between Service Outages: UpTime/OutageCount or zero if OutageCount = 0 (in seconds).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTTSR.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTTSR
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTTSR.description: Mean Time to ServiceRestoral: DownTime/OutageCount or zero if OutageCount = 0 (in seconds).

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEncapType.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEncapType
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEncapType.description: The encapsulation protocol seen in the last frame analyzed on this DLCI: (1) DLCI is the LMI DLCI or no frames have been analyzed (2) The encapsulation is per rfc1490 (3) The encapsulation is per Cisco proprietary (4) The encapsulation is per Annex-G (X.25 over frame relay) (5) The encapsulation is not one of the above.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxUtilizationStat.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxUtilizationStatus
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxUtilizationStat.description: The status of the per-DLCI utilization alarm in the receive direction. (1) there is no alarm condition; utilization is under the configured CIR percentage threshold; if traps are enabled and the alarm had been previously triggered, a utilization alarm clear trap will be sent. (2) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration. (3) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for more than the configured duration; if traps are enabled a utilization exceeded trap will be sent. (4) the utilization has been under the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxUtilizationStat.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxUtilizationStatus
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxUtilizationStat.description: The status of the per-DLCI utilization alarm in the transmit direction. (1) there is no alarm condition; utilization is under the configured CIR percentage threshold; if traps are enabled and the alarm had been previously triggered, a utilization alarm clear trap will be sent. (2) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration. (3) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for more than the configured duration; if traps are enabled a utilization exceeded trap will be sent. (4) the utilization has been under the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration.

dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEIR.name: dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEIR
dfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEIR.description: The Excess Information Rate. This is defined to be the maximum rate traffic is (supposed to be) allowed to burst to.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDteStats.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDteStats
dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDteStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the interface statistics in the DTE portion of the ThruputPerIntf statistics table. (1) Clear DTE interface statistics command.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDdsStats.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDdsStats
dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDdsStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the interface statistics in the DDS portion of the ThruputPerIntf statistics table. (1) Clear WAN interface statistics command.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllIntfStats.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllIntfStats
dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllIntfStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the statistics in the ThruputPerIntf statistics table.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDlciStats.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDlciStats
dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDlciStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the per-DLCI statistics in the ThruputPerDlci statistics table and the the short term statistics tables. (1) Clear layer 2 per-DLCI statistics command.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllStats.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllStats
dfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the statistics in the ThruputPerIntf and ThruputPerDlci statistics tables and in the short term statistics tables. (1) Clear all interface and layer 2 per-DLCI statistics.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdRemoveStsDlci.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdRemoveStsDlci
dfrapPerfThruputCmdRemoveStsDlci.description: Allows the user to remove a Dlci from the short term statistics tables.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciTable.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciTable
dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciTable.description: Allows the user to replace one DLCI in the short-term statistics table with another one.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciEntry.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciEntry
dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciEntry.description: Allows the user to replace one DLCI in the short-term statistics table with another one.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciValue.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciValue
dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciValue.description: A Dlci that is in the short-term stats table. Index by this Dlci value to identify the statistics entry to be replaced.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciNewValue.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciNewValue
dfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciNewValue.description: A Dlci that is to replace another in the short-term stats table. Index by this Dlci value to identify the statistics entry to do the replacing.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciReset
dfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.description: Allows the user to reset the availability statistics of an individual Dlci within the short-term stats table.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciResetAll
dfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.description: Allows the user to reset the availability statistics of all Dlci's within the short-term stats table.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciReset.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciReset
dfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciReset.description: Allows the user to reset the count statistics of an individual Dlci within the short-term stats table.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciResetAll.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciResetAll
dfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciResetAll.description: Allows the user to reset the count statistics of all Dlci's within the short-term stats table.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciReset.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciReset
dfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciReset.description: Allows the user to reset both the count and availability statistics of an individual Dlci within the short-term stats table.

dfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciResetAll.name: dfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciResetAll
dfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciResetAll.description: Allows the user to reset both the count and the availability statistics of all Dlci's within the short-term stats table.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTable.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTable
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTable.description: The Short Term Statistics on the Network Layer protocol for each DLCI. These are protocol-based per-DLCI statistics. The Short Term model maintains three intervals: current, previous, and cumulative totals. Interval duration is defined by the Short Term Timer (CfgFrPerfTimersSTInterval).

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciEntry.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciEntry
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciEntry.description: The Network Layer Short Term Statistics for a particular DLCI. This table organizes statistics by high-layer network protocol.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciInterval.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciInterval
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciInterval.description: The Short Term statistics model maintains three intervals: current, previous, and cumulative totals. Interval duration is defined by the Short Term Timer (CfgFrPerfTimersSTInterval). (1) Currently active short term interval (2) Previously completed short term interval (3) Cumulative total since last cleared.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciValue.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciValue
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciValue.description: The DLCI value with which the Statistics are associated.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxTotal.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxTotal
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxTotal.description: The total number of received Network Layer bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxTotal.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxTotal
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxTotal.description: The total number of transmitted Network Layer bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIp.description: The number of received IP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIp.description: The number of transmitted IP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIpx.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIpx
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIpx.description: The number of received IPX bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIpx.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIpx
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIpx.description: The number of transmitted IPX bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxSna.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxSna
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxSna.description: The number of received SNA bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxSna.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxSna
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxSna.description: The number of transmitted SNA bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxArp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxArp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxArp.description: The number of received ARP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxArp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxArp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxArp.description: The number of transmitted ARP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxCisco.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxCisco
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxCisco.description: The number of received Cisco protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxCisco.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxCisco
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxCisco.description: The number of transmitted Cisco protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxOther.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxOther
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxOther.description: The number of received bytes on this DLCI from protocols that are not counted elsewhere in this table.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxOther.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxOther
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxOther.description: The number of transmitted bytes on this DLCI from protocols that are not counted elsewhere in this table.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxVnip.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxVnip
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxVnip.description: The number of received VNIP protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxVnip.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxVnip
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxVnip.description: The number of transmitted VNIP protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxAnnexG.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxAnnexG
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxAnnexG.description: The number of received Annex G protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxAnnexG.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxAnnexG
dfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxAnnexG.description: The number of transmitted Annex G protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTable.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTable
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTable.description: The Short Term Statistics on Network Layer protocols summed across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalEntry.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalEntry
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalEntry.description: The Network Layer Short Term Statistics across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalInterval.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalInterval
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalInterval.description: The Short Term statistics model maintains three intervals: current, previous, and cumulative totals. Interval duration is defined by the Short Term Timer (CfgFrPerfTimersSTInterval). (1) Currently active short term interval (2) Previously completed short term interval (3) Cumulative total since last cleared.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxTotal.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxTotal
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxTotal.description: The total number of received Network Layer bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxTotal.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxTotal
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxTotal.description: The total number of transmitted Network Layer bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIp.description: The number of received IP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIp.description: The number of transmitted IP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIpx.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIpx
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIpx.description: The number of received IPX bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIpx.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIpx
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIpx.description: The number of transmitted IPX bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxSna.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxSna
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxSna.description: The number of received SNA bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxSna.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxSna
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxSna.description: The number of transmitted SNA bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxArp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxArp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxArp.description: The number of received ARP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxArp.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxArp
dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxArp.description: The number of transmitted ARP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxCisco.name: dfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxCisco

dfrapLocalDteLoopbackEnabledTrap.description: Unit is in a bi-directional DTE loopback. All data received at the DTE interface is looped back regardless of format or content (line loopback). All data received at the WAN interface is looped back regardless of format or content (line loopback) When configured for Frame Relay operation the unit will not preserve the LMI path during this loopback.

dfrapLocalDteLoopbackDisabledTrap.name: dfrapLocalDteLoopbackDisabledTrap
dfrapLocalDteLoopbackDisabledTrap.description: Bi-directional DTE loopback path is removed.

dfrapLocalDteLoopbackFailedTrap.name: dfrapLocalDteLoopbackFailedTrap
dfrapLocalDteLoopbackFailedTrap.description: Bi-directional DTE loopback request has been rejected by the unit. Typically, this is due to the presence of another loopback condition.

dfrapLocalNetLoopbackEnabledTrap.name: dfrapLocalNetLoopbackEnabledTrap
dfrapLocalNetLoopbackEnabledTrap.description: Unit is in local network loopback. All data received from the WAN, regardless of format or content, is transmitted back out (line interface loopback) while still being sent to the DTE. When configured for Frame Relay operation the unit will not preserve the LMI path during this loopback.

dfrapLocalNetLoopbackDisabledTrap.name: dfrapLocalNetLoopbackDisabledTrap
dfrapLocalNetLoopbackDisabledTrap.description: Local network loopback path is removed.

dfrapLocalNetLoopbackFailedTrap.name: dfrapLocalNetLoopbackFailedTrap
dfrapLocalNetLoopbackFailedTrap.description: Local network loopback request is rejected. Typically, this is due to the presence of another loopback condition.

dfrapV54LoopUpInitiatedTrap.name: dfrapV54LoopUpInitiatedTrap
dfrapV54LoopUpInitiatedTrap.description: Unit has sent the standard V54 loop up pattern out the WAN at the DTE rate. A compatible piece of equipment can sense this pattern and enter a loopback state - typically putting up a bi-directional DTE loopback path. After sending the V54 loop up pattern, the (local) unit returns to normal operation, expecting a loopback condition at the remote device.

dfrapV54LoopDownCompletedTrap.name: dfrapV54LoopDownCompletedTrap
dfrapV54LoopDownCompletedTrap.description: Unit has sent the standard V54 loop down pattern out the WAN at the DTE rate. A compatible piece of equipment can sense this pattern remove the loopback state that is entered after receiving a loop up pattern - typically a bi-directional DTE loopback path. After sending the V54 loop down pattern, the unit returns to normal operation.

dfrapV54LoopbackEnabledTrap.name: dfrapV54LoopbackEnabledTrap
dfrapV54LoopbackEnabledTrap.description: Unit has received a V54 loop up pattern from a compatible piece of equipment. A bi-directional DTE loopback is activated. All data received at the DTE interface is looped back regardless of format or content. All data received at the WAN interface is looped back regardless of format or content. When configured for Frame Relay operation the unit will not preserve the LMI path during this loopback.

dfrapV54LoopbackDisabledTrap.name: dfrapV54LoopbackDisabledTrap
dfrapV54LoopbackDisabledTrap.description: Unit has received a V54 loop down pattern from a compatible piece of equipment. The bi-directional local DTE loopback is removed

dfrapV54LoopbackFailedTrap.name: dfrapV54LoopbackFailedTrap
dfrapV54LoopbackFailedTrap.description: Unit has rejected the request to send a V54 loop up. Typically, this is due to the presence of another loopback condition.

dfrapBertInitiatedTrap.name: dfrapBertInitiatedTrap
dfrapBertInitiatedTrap.description: Unit is sending a pseudorandom test pattern (511 or QRSS) out the WAN and monitoring the WAN received data for the same pattern. This test may be ineffective in certain frame relay applications as pseudorandom data lacks appropriate framing.

dfrapBertCompletedTrap.name: dfrapBertCompletedTrap
dfrapBertCompletedTrap.description: Unit has stopped sending a pseudorandom test pattern out the WAN.

dfrapBertFailedTrap.name: dfrapBertFailedTrap
dfrapBertFailedTrap.description: Unit has rejected the request to enter a BERT test state. Typically, this is due to the presence of another diagnostic condition.

dfrapDLCIActiveTrap.name: dfrapDLCIActiveTrap
dfrapDLCIActiveTrap.description: Unit is reporting this DLCI as active and provisioned. An active DLCI is one that is explicitly declared ACTIVE in an LMI Full Status Response (typically coming from a frame relay switch).

dfrapDLCIInactiveTrap.name: dfrapDLCIInactiveTrap
dfrapDLCIInactiveTrap.description: Unit is reporting this DLCI as inactive. An inactive DLCI is determined inactive one of two ways: it is either explicitly declared inactive in an LMI Full Status Response (typically coming from a frame relay switch) or a Full Status Response is not seen causing a Full Status Timer expiry. Having the unit's full status timer too low could result in the unit falsely declaring DLCIs inactive (then active again). This does not interfere with any data activity on the DLCI but could result in excessive traps.

dfrapDLCITDThresholdTrap.name: dfrapDLCITDThresholdTrap
dfrapDLCITDThresholdTrap.description: VNIP has measured a round-trip transit delay on this PVC to this peer which exceeds the user-defined threshold.

dfrapLmiSourcingChangePassthruTrap.name: dfrapLmiSourcingChangePassthruTrap
dfrapLmiSourcingChangePassthruTrap.description: Unit is not sourcing any LMI messages. If this state persists then LMI is up and the proper handshaking is occurring independent of the unit. This may also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

dfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserDteTrap.name: dfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserDteTrap
dfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserDteTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Requests (Link Integrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equipment attached to the DTE interface is configured as a Frame Relay DCE but a companion Frame Relay DTE device is not seen out the WAN. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

dfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetDteTrap.name: dfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetDteTrap
dfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetDteTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Responses (Link Integrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equipment attached to the DTE interface is configured as a Frame Relay DTE but a companion Frame Relay DCE device is not seen out the WAN. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of external equipment.

dfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserDdsTrap.name: dfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserDdsTrap
dfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserDdsTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Requests (Link Integrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equipment attached to the WAN interface is configured as a Frame Relay DCE but a companion Frame Relay DTE device is not seen out the DTE interface. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

dfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetDdsTrap.name: dfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetDdsTrap
dfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetDdsTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Responses (Link Integrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equipment attached to the WAN interface is configured as a Frame Relay DTE but a companion Frame Relay DCE device is not seen out the DTE interface. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

dfrapDteSignalRtsOnTrap.name: dfrapDteSignalRtsOnTrap
dfrapDteSignalRtsOnTrap.description: Unit's DTE Request to Send (RTS) interface control signal is now active (on). This signal is presented by the external DTE device.

dfrapDteSignalRtsOffTrap.name: dfrapDteSignalRtsOffTrap
dfrapDteSignalRtsOffTrap.description: Unit's DTE Request to Send (RTS) interface control signal is now inactive (off). This signal is presented by the external DTE device.

dfrapDteSignalDtrOnTrap.name: dfrapDteSignalDtrOnTrap
dfrapDteSignalDtrOnTrap.description: Unit's DTE Data Terminal Ready (DTR) interface control signal is now active (on). This signal is presented by the external DTE device.

dfrapDteSignalDtrOffTrap.name: dfrapDteSignalDtrOffTrap
dfrapDteSignalDtrOffTrap.description: Unit's DTE Data Terminal Ready (DTR) interface control signal is now inactive (off). This signal is presented by the external DTE device.

dfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumDteTrap.name: dfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumDteTrap
dfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumDteTrap.description: Unit has detected a non-incrementing LMI sequence number from the DTE. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the DTE interface. The Link Integrity information element's Send Sequence Number was not incremented or was incremented more than once since the last Send Sequence Number seen from the DTE interface.

dfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumDdsTrap.name: dfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumDdsTrap
dfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumDdsTrap.description: Unit has detected a non-incrementing LMI sequence number from the WAN. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the WAN interface. The Link Integrity information element's Send Sequence Number was not incremented or was incremented more than once since the last Send Sequence Number seen from the WAN interface.

dfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchDteTrap.name: dfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchDteTrap
dfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchDteTrap.description: Unit has detected an LMI sequence number mismatch from the DTE. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the DTE interface. The Link Inetgrity information element's Receive Sequence Number was not the most recent Send Sequence number sent from the WAN interface

dfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchDdsTrap.name: dfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchDdsTrap
dfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchDdsTrap.description: Unit has detected an LMI sequence number mismatch from the WAN. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the WAN interface. The Link Integrity information element's Receive Sequence Number was not the most recent Send Sequence number sent from the DTE interface.

dfrapLineFailureTrap.name: dfrapLineFailureTrap
dfrapLineFailureTrap.description: The unit is reporting error conditions that inditate that the WAN connection is not fully functional.

dfrapLineInServiceTrap.name: dfrapLineInServiceTrap
dfrapLineInServiceTrap.description: The unit is reporting that its WAN link has transitioned from a failure state to one which is functioning normally.

dfrapBPVThresholdExceededTrap.name: dfrapBPVThresholdExceededTrap
dfrapBPVThresholdExceededTrap.description: The unit may be configured to issue this alarm in response to line code violations being received from the service provider. If more than 5 violations are detected within a one-second interval, this trap is generated. Network control codes which include bipolar violations are not considered errors and will not contribute to this trap. If this condition persists then contact your WAN service provider.

dfrapBPVThresholdAcceptableTrap.name: dfrapBPVThresholdAcceptableTrap
dfrapBPVThresholdAcceptableTrap.description: This trap is to announce that the bipolar violation threshold of at least 5 per second is no longer being exceeded.

dfrapSimplexCurrentLoopbackEnabledTrap.name: dfrapSimplexCurrentLoopbackEnabledTrap
dfrapSimplexCurrentLoopbackEnabledTrap.description: The unit has received a DDS-standard simplex current reversal from the WAN. In response, a Network Line Loopback path will be initiated for the duration of the current reversal.

dfrapSimplexCurrentLoopbackDisabledTrap.name: dfrapSimplexCurrentLoopbackDisabledTrap
dfrapSimplexCurrentLoopbackDisabledTrap.description: The unit has ceased receiving a simplex current reversal from the WAN. In response, the Network Line Loopback path will be removed.

dfrapNonLatchingLoopbackEnabledTrap.name: dfrapNonLatchingLoopbackEnabledTrap
dfrapNonLatchingLoopbackEnabledTrap.description: The unit has received a DDS-standard in-band loopback command. In response, a Network Line Loopback path will be initiated and maintained as long as the appropriate command is recognized.

dfrapNonLatchingLoopbackDisabledTrap.name: dfrapNonLatchingLoopbackDisabledTrap
dfrapNonLatchingLoopbackDisabledTrap.description: The unit has ceased receiving a DDS-standard in-band loopback command. In response, a Network Line Loopback path will be removed.

dfrapTrapMutingActive.name: dfrapTrapMutingActive
dfrapTrapMutingActive.description: Trap generation is muted. This trap will be issued at the configured trap muting frequency. No other traps will be issued.

dfrapVloopUp.name: dfrapVloopUp
dfrapVloopUp.description: A Vnip PVC loopback (VLOOP) request has been sent to a remote device on this DLCI out this interface. The remote unit should respond by looping all data received on this PVC back towards the unit that initiated this request. A PVC running VLOOP will not be running any user data.

dfrapVloopDown.name: dfrapVloopDown
dfrapVloopDown.description: A Vnip PVC loopback (VLOOP) disable request has been sent to a remote device on this DLCI out this interface. The remote unit should respond by tearing down the logical loop on this DLCI.

dfrapVloopUpViaRemote.name: dfrapVloopUpViaRemote
dfrapVloopUpViaRemote.description: A Vnip PVC loopback (VLOOP) request has been received from a remote device on this DLCI on this interface. The unit will respond by looping all data received on this PVC back out the interface towards the unit that initiated the request.

dfrapVloopDownViaRemote.name: dfrapVloopDownViaRemote
dfrapVloopDownViaRemote.description: A request to disable a Vnip PVC loopback (VLOOP) on this unit with the indicated DLCI and Interface has been received. Usually this disable request is from the remote device that requested the VLOOP, however the request may also be due to a local event such as expiration of a locally configured loopback timeout. The unit will respond by tearing down the logical loop on this DLCI.

dfrapVloopRequestFailed.name: dfrapVloopRequestFailed
dfrapVloopRequestFailed.description: The request for a PVC loopback (VLOOP) has been rejected or did not complete.

dfrapVbertStarted.name: dfrapVbertStarted
dfrapVbertStarted.description: A Vnip PVC error rate test (VBERT) has been started on this DLCI out this interface to a remote device. The VBERT test data will be statistically multiplexed in with user data, management data, and networking data. The destination peer will echo this test data back to the source producing a full-duplex volume-based timed test.

dfrapVbertStopped.name: dfrapVbertStopped
dfrapVbertStopped.description: A Vnip PVC BERT (VBERT) has been stopped on this DLCI on this interface to a remote device.

dfrapVbertRequestFailed.name: dfrapVbertRequestFailed
dfrapVbertRequestFailed.description: The request for a PVC BERT (VBERT) on this DLCI on this interface has been rejected.

dfrapPvcRxUtilizationExceededTrap.name: dfrapPvcRxUtilizationExceededTrap
dfrapPvcRxUtilizationExceededTrap.description: Percent utilization threshold was exceeded for the defined number of Short Term Intervals in the reception direction on this DLCI.

dfrapPvcTxUtilizationExceededTrap.name: dfrapPvcTxUtilizationExceededTrap
dfrapPvcTxUtilizationExceededTrap.description: Percent utilization threshold was exceeded for the defined number of Short Term Intervals in the transmission direction on this DLCI.

dfrapPvcRxUtilizationClearedTrap.name: dfrapPvcRxUtilizationClearedTrap
dfrapPvcRxUtilizationClearedTrap.description: Percent utilization was below the threshold for the defined number of Short Term Intervals in the reception direction on this DLCI.

dfrapPvcTxUtilizationClearedTrap.name: dfrapPvcTxUtilizationClearedTrap
dfrapPvcTxUtilizationClearedTrap.description: Percent utilization was below the threshold for the defined number of Short Term Intervals in the transmission direction on this DLCI.

dfrapConfigInstallSuccess.name: dfrapConfigInstallSuccess
dfrapConfigInstallSuccess.description: The configuration install process has successfully completed.

dfrapTftpRequestedTrap.name: dfrapTftpRequestedTrap
dfrapTftpRequestedTrap.description: Unit has received a TFTP download request. TFTP is the preferred method for upgrading a unit's software image.

dfrapTftpTransferringTrap.name: dfrapTftpTransferringTrap
dfrapTftpTransferringTrap.description: Unit has established a TFTP session, found the file, and begun the transfer. The file must still be qualified as appropriate for this unit.

dfrapTftpProgrammingTrap.name: dfrapTftpProgrammingTrap
dfrapTftpProgrammingTrap.description: Unit has completed the TFTP transfer of a new software image which will next be programmed into non-volatile flash memory

dfrapTftpAbortedTrap.name: dfrapTftpAbortedTrap
dfrapTftpAbortedTrap.description: Unit's TFTP session was established but the transfer was aborted by user intervention or an unrecoverable TFTP protocol error

dfrapTftpSuccessTrap.name: dfrapTftpSuccessTrap
dfrapTftpSuccessTrap.description: Unit's TFTP download completed successfully. Flash devices will be programmed with a new image. Unit will stop passing data during the programming phase (less than a minute) and, upon completion, will reset and return to full operation using the new image

dfrapTftpHostUnreachableTrap.name: dfrapTftpHostUnreachableTrap
dfrapTftpHostUnreachableTrap.description: Unit could not establish a TFTP session with the designated server. Verify that the correct TFTP ip address, TFTP DLCI and TFTP interface are configured on the unit and also verify the TFTP server configuration

dfrapTftpNoFileTrap.name: dfrapTftpNoFileTrap
dfrapTftpNoFileTrap.description: Unit could not locate the designated file on the TFTP server. Verify the correct TFTP filename is configured on the unit and verify the location of this file on the server (file name may be case sensitive)

dfrapTftpInvalidFileTrap.name: dfrapTftpInvalidFileTrap
dfrapTftpInvalidFileTrap.description: Unit had established a TFTP session and began transfer of the designated file. The unit aborted the transfer after determining that the specified file is not appropriate for this product (failed header verification)

dfrapTftpCorruptFileTrap.name: dfrapTftpCorruptFileTrap
dfrapTftpCorruptFileTrap.description: Unit transferred the designated file but aborted the operation due to a checksum error within the downloaded s-record file
